The paper deals with modeling constraints on the order in which states of an automaton are transitioned by a synchronizing word. This falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) as it involves the study of discrete structures such as automata and words. Additionally, the paper also deals with modeling and computation, which could fall under the categories of Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The use of automata and constraints to solve a practical problem also suggests that the paper could be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
